<br>
The examples you cite are great.  If they happened then you are right and Bush is a hypocrite, but still comes down to me never saying he wasn't.<br>
<br>
Bush doesn't represent me real well, no candidate in office ever will.  Lets not confuse the issues here.  I am not comparing presidents other than George and Bill.  I don't care if Abraham Lincoln was screwing his secret ring of enslaved harlots... well I do inasmuch as it relates to the morality and pride of the nation.  <br>
<br>
To me a man stands on his own merits... not what his father did or did not do, and certainly not compared to other men.  Clinton wasn't as bas as so and so, so we should just accept the stupid things he did do??  That’s a pretty great way to do things huh?<br>
<br>
<br>
George Bush has his issues, most of which I am probably not aware because I usually don't delve to deep into politics, if it doesn't make the headlines I probably don't see it. The thing about George is that I think he is mostly sincere.  I am not talking about his foreign policies, or his tax cuts... I am saying that I think he means what he says and really wants what’s best for everyone.  Pause here and remember I don't think he's perfect.<br>
<br>
Bill, on the other hand, strikes me as an opportunist.  He always looks like he is hiding something.  He always seems like he is looking out for himself.  When he speaks you can almost see in his eyes that he is thinking something else.  I am a pretty good judge of people, always have been (pause here to remember I didn't say I am always right), and he just always rubbed me wrong.<br>
<br>
I won't support Bush just because he is Republican.  I won't rag on Clinton because he is Democrat.  Parties mean nothing to me... except a reference point that I as a conservative person will most likely agree with a republican on a matter that is important to me.  That is a generalization though as there are some democrats that are more conservative than some republicans.  I didn't vote for Bush in the elections, I voted against Gore by pressing the button for Bush.<br>
<br>
I am not really aware of the stereotypes of the two parties.  I forget - as a republican am I for gun control or against?  Am I for or against big programs that pay lazy people to sit home?  Feel free to fill me in on what my party stands for cause I only pick one so I can go vote on the person who I believe cares more about making change.  No, that isn't a speech or a personal attack on anyone, just my true naive stance on voting.<br>
<br>
Anyway, back to the Clinton thing.  My statement:  <font color=yellow>You either know enough about both of them to know why I say it or you are too stupid to reason with. Either way it is a waste of time to tell you. </font color>  Wasn't really the best way to state it.  My point is that if you think democrats are better then you obviously aren't based on facts so arguing with you is a waste.  Sure, its a generalization, but its an accurate one 9/10 times.<br>
<br>
